result.text:
🇨🇳#China's special envoy on the Middle East Issue Zhai Jun attended the summit on the Palestinian question held in Cairo yesterday. Key points of Zhai's remarks:

➡️China opposes & condemns all actions that harm civilians and any violations of international law.

➡️ China urges an immediate halt to military operations & the opening of humanitarian relief channels. 

➡️The international community should be objective, impartial and practical in promoting a comprehensive, just & permanent solution to the Palestinian issue ASAP.

➡️The fundamental way out lies in implementing the "two-state solution" & establishing an independent State of Palestine.

➡️China will continue to work with all relevant parties & the international community to de-escalate the conflict, support the Palestinian people's just cause of restoring their legitimate national rights, implement the "two-state solution" and push for lasting peace & security in the Middle East region.
#PalestinianIsraeliconflict

legacy.description: 12th Chinese Ambassador to the United States
legacy.name: Xie Feng 谢锋

result.text:
Today, Foreign Minister Wang Yi had a phone conversation with Secretary Blinken on the ongoing Palestine-Israel conflict. 

Foreign Minister Wang pointed out that the top priority is to achieve a ceasefire and deescalate the situation to avoid aggravating the humanitarian disaster; to abide by the international humanitarian law and open corridors for humanitarian aid; and to support the UN in pooling international consensus and the Security Council in playing its due role. 

"There is no way out through military means, and using violence to fight against violence will only create a vicious cycle," said Wang.

The two sides also briefly exchanged views on China-US relations.
